# Trivy ignore list — transitive vulnerabilities that cannot be safely fixed
# via pnpm.overrides without breaking a consumer. Each entry documents why it
# is accepted. Review periodically.

# valibot ReDoS in EMOJI_REGEX (CVE-2025-66020)
# Source: sats-connect@3.0.1 -> @sats-connect/core@0.4.1 -> valibot@0.42.1
#         (used only by @to-nexus/appkit-adapter-bitcoin)
# Why accepted: the only patched line is valibot@1.x, a breaking major that
# @sats-connect/core@0.4.1 does not support (forcing it fails the bitcoin
# adapter typecheck). The ReDoS is in an emoji-validation regex that is not on
# the wallet-connect input path, so it is not exploitable in this context.
# Remove once sats-connect ships a release built against valibot@1.x.
CVE-2025-66020
